Workflow

Learn how data flows through the configurations when you welcome new loyalty members to your program.

Workflow for the Loyalty Welcome Journey

Shopper joins the Loyalty Program by signing up online or in-store.
The Commerce and OMS systems send the member and order information to Loyalty Management using the API.
Loyalty Management receives member enrollment and updates membership tiers and points based on the defined loyalty programs.
A Salesforce data entry event identifies the new loyalty program member and triggers a Marketing Cloud Engagement Loyalty Welcome journey.
Understanding the Flow of Data

To send member information and reward transactions to Loyalty Management from Commerce, OMS, and POS systems, implement API processes.
To replicate loyalty data in Marketing Cloud Engagement, implement Marketing Cloud Connect and synchronize Loyalty Management data extensions.
To enter subscribed loyalty members into a Loyalty Welcome Journey, use a Salesforce Data Entry Event.
